Raspberry PI board configuration:

Raspberry PI Image:
2014-09-09-wheezy-raspbian.img
Upons setup all settings are left at default

Cofinure ALSA
 sudo nano /etc/modprobe.d/alsa-base.conf
Now change this
   # Keep snd-usb-audio from being loaded as first soundcard 
   options snd-usb-audio index=-2
To
   options snd-usb-audio index=0

================  TEST ALSA installation ============
pi@raspberrypi ~ $ cat /proc/asound/cards 
 0 [DSP            ]: USB-Audio - Plantronics .Audio 400 DSP
                      Plantronics Plantronics .Audio 400 DSP at usb-bcm2708_usb-1.3, full speed
 1 [ALSA           ]: bcm2835 - bcm2835 ALSA
                      bcm2835 ALSA

pi@raspberrypi ~ $ arecord  -f  S16_LE -c 2 -r 44100 -vv test.wav
<Say something to microphone> 

pi@raspberrypi ~ $ aplay  test.wav
<Should hear what you've said>

== Install SPHINX ==
# Install prerequsites 
sudo apt-get install bison
sudo apt-get install libasound2-dev

# 
tar xvzf sphinxbase-0.8.tar.gz
cd sphinxbase-0.8
./configure --enable-fixed
make
sudo make install

#
tar xvzf pocketsphinx-0.8.tar.gz 
cd pocketsphinx-0.8
./configure 
make
sudo make install


